## Sprint History

### Sprint 1 ‚Äî Foundation
- CSV loading with `@st.cache_data`
- Column name normalization via `.str.strip()`
- Timestamp construction from separate Date/Time columns

### Sprint 2 ‚Äî Visualizations
- `px.scatter_mapbox` for spatial distribution
- `px.line` for temporal trends
- Two-column layout with `st.columns`

### Sprint 3 ‚Äî User Controls
- `st.sidebar.selectbox` for metric selection
- `st.sidebar.slider` for sample size
- `st.table` for statistical summary
- `st.expander` for raw data view

### Sprint 4 ‚Äî Advanced Analytics
- Dark ocean CSS theme with Google Fonts
- KPI metric cards (HTML/CSS grid via `st.markdown`)
- Depth profile: `groupby('depth_bin').agg(['mean','std'])` + `go.Scatter` with `error_x`
- Correlation matrix: `df.corr()` + `go.Heatmap` with `RdBu_r` colorscale
- Rolling average: `.rolling(window=20, center=True).mean()`
- Anomaly detection: `(x - mean).abs() > 2 * std`
- Scatter + OLS: `px.scatter(trendline='ols')` (requires statsmodels)
- Histogram: `go.Histogram` + `add_vline` for mean/median
- CSV download: `st.download_button` with `df.to_csv().encode('utf-8')`

